    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static <T> T create(Class<T> type,
           Object... args)
                throws ReflectiveOperationException
        Creates a remote CloudObjects of the desired type using the given parameters for the remote constructor invocation.

        Note that the created proxy does not redirect method invocations to the corresponding CloudObject.
        Instead invoke(Object, java.lang.reflect.Method, Object...) must be used in order to access the remote object.

        Parameters:
        type - the type of the object to create
        args - the constructor arguments
        Returns:
        a proxy for the remote object
        Throws:
        ReflectiveOperationException - if an exception occurred during object creation

      • create

        public static <T> T create(Constructor<?> constructor,
           Class<T> type,
           Object... args)
        Creates a remote CloudObject using the given proxy and parameters for the remote constructor invocation.

        Note that this method is intended to be used by JCloudScale internally.
        It is recommended to use create(Class, Object...) instead.

        Parameters:
        constructor - the constructor to use
        type - the type of the object to create
        args - the constructor arguments
        Returns:
        the proxy
        Throws:
        NoSuchMethodException - if there are zero or more than one constructor candidates
        See Also:
        create(Class, Object...)

      • destroy

        public static void destroy(Object obj)
        Destroys the remote object associated with the given proxy.
        If this method is invoked for a destroyed CloudObject, it simply does nothing.
        Parameters:
        obj - the proxy of the object to destroy.

        Returns:
        the result of the method invocation

      • getId

        public static UUID getId(Object obj)
        Returns the unique identifier of the proxy.

        Note that the identifiers are preserved even if the objects are already destroyed.

        Parameters:
        obj - the proxy
        Returns:
        the unique identifier or null if the object is no known cloud object

      • isCloudObject

        public static boolean isCloudObject(UUID id)
        Checks whether the given id belongs to a known available cloud object.
        A cloud object is available until it has been marked for destruction.
        Parameters:
        id - the unique identifier to query
        Returns:
        true if there is a remote cloud object with the given ID, false otherwise.

      • isDestroyed

        public static boolean isDestroyed(UUID id)
        Checks whether the given id belongs to a cloud object that is already destroyed.
        Parameters:
        id - the unique identifier to query
        Returns:
        true if a cloud object was associated with the given identifier, false otherwise.
